Mombasa senator aspirant Hamisi Mwaguya has kicked off his campaign and women are a major target. Women comprise the highest percentage of voters. On Saturday, Mwaguya visited the Coast Provincial General Hospital maternity wing and spent time with mothers. Mwaguya served in the Mombasa government as a county secretary before he was transferred to Trade department. The aspirant, seeking the ODM ticket, said he will ensure maternal health improves. &ldquo;There is need for the national and the county governments to work together to improve the maternal health in the country,&rdquo; Mwaguya said. He said during the doctors&rsquo; strike, mothers and children suffered most. Mwaguya said he will push to have more money allocated to the health sector.